{{Youmay|the creature|the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Ratrin Vhek]]}}
{{Quote|Have you tried dragging a whole merlie or vhek home for dinner?|Jinart, to Omega Squad|<ref name="RC:HC">''[[Republic Commando: Hard Contact]]''</ref>}}
'''Vheks''' were creatures found<ref name="RC:HC" /> on the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> [[Qiilura/Legends|Qiilura]] that were known to be preyed upon by packs of [[gdan]]s.<ref name="RC:HC" /> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[Republic Commando: Hard Contact]]'', which includes the mention of vheks, in the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref> the [[Gurlanin]] [[Jinart]] asked the [[Omega Squad]]'s [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] if they had ever dragged an intact vhek home for a meal, indicating that gdans worked together to catch one of the creatures and then dragged their bounty away via large tunnels.<ref name="RC:HC" />

==Behind the scenes==
Vheks were mentioned in the [[2004]] novel ''[[Republic Commando: Hard Contact|Hard Contact]]'', the first novel in the ''[[Republic Commando]]'' series written by [[Karen Traviss]].<ref name="RC:HC" />

